opening_comment: The place-node for Bangui has a weird character encoding set for its name tags in several different languages. As far as I can tell, this issue exists since version 18 (about 1 year ago).
closing_comment: Well. In that wiki they say you can map a place as an area. In that case, the name would be the geometrical centre of that area. In my case, I just put it in roughly what would be the center or the big residential area of Bangui ( http://www.openstreetmap.org/way/102336004 ). But the node is also quite centered in what respects to facilities, with the Assemblée Nationale to the East, the Airport to the West and the sport stadiums of the Stade Complexe Barthélémy Boganda to the SE. It's also placed more or less in the center of the main avenues, between the Avenue de l'Independance, the Avenue de France and the Avenue des Martyrs. It's difficult to decide in fact what the best location should be for a place node, but being placed in the PK0 SE corner of the city is less optimal, IMHO, than putting it further north, were it is now.
